docs.lead_paragraph: JOHN W. WEEKE has been appointed Inspector of Hulle, and H. RENWICK Inspector of Bollers in New-York, by the Secretary of the Treasury. The following have been confirmed in the Senate: WM. R. SMITH, Collector, Galveston, vice JOHN B. ASHS, whose commission was revoked. FREDRICK L. HENNUP, appraiser for Philadelphia, Vice JOHN H. WITHERS removed.

byline.original: By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times.Special Dispatch to New-York Daily Times

docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Houston arrived to-day, direct from Texas, in good health. The Hon. GRAHAM N. FITCH has gone to Indiana, to be about at the meeting of the Legislature next week, and will be returned Senator for the unexpired term of the late Mr. WHITECOMB.
